.head 3 -  ! The next two push button classes go hand in hand
.head 3 +  Pushbutton Class: JanSelectFromTablePbClass
.head 4 -  Title:
.head 4 -  Window Location and Size
.head 5 -  Left:
.head 5 -  Top:
.head 5 -  Width:  Class Default
.head 5 -  Width Editable? Class Default
.head 5 -  Height: Class Default
.head 5 -  Height Editable? Class Default
.head 4 -  Visible? Class Default
.head 4 -  Keyboard Accelerator: Class Default
.head 4 -  Font Name: Class Default
.head 4 -  Font Size: Class Default
.head 4 -  Font Enhancement: Class Default
.head 4 -  Picture File Name:
.head 4 -  Picture Transparent Color: Class Default
.head 4 -  Image Style: Class Default
.head 4 -  Text Color: Class Default
.head 4 -  Background Color: Class Default
.head 4 -  List in Tool Palette? Yes
.head 4 -  Property Template:
.head 4 -  Class DLL Name:
.head 4 -  Button Appearance: Class Default
.head 4 -  Description: Use this push button class to implement a select button to select data from a table window
into another window.  This class talks with JanPickIntoTablePbClass to achive its selections.
INSTANCE VARIABLES :
  hWndTable : refers to the ussually child table on hWndForm which is being selected from
  hWndSelectParent : refers to the button (JanPickIntoTablePbClass) that should have
                                   created hWndForm
  bManytoManySelect : Default is TRUE, this specifies that selecting multiple rows will select
                                      into the corresponding selected rows and when the select into 
                                      selected rows run out (ie:not enough) PAM_ADDROW is send to
                                      add a ROW_New until all the user selected rows have been processed.
  bOneToManySelect : Default is FALSE, this allows one user select to be selected into
                                     many selected rows.
  nSelectDirection : Values are nLowToHi , nHiToLow, nLowToHiWithPositioning, 
                                nHiToLowWithPositioning.  Purpose is the way the user selected selected rows
                                get processed from top to bottom or bottom to top.
  MESSAGES TO IMPLEMENT PER INSTANCE
    PAM_PUSHFIELDS  : Must return TRUE
    PAM_POPFIELDS : Must return TRUE, should pop off the data pushed in PAM_PUSHFIELDS
                                   message.  ( HAS TO BE IMPLEMENTED )
    PAM_LOOKUPFINISH : Trap this message to implement the destroy or hide of the pick screen
                                          once the selection process has been completed.
