.head 4 -  Class DLL Name:
.head 4 -  Button Appearance: Class Default
.head 4 -  Description: Use this button class to implement a PICK button that creates a window from which the user
can select rows to select back into hWndForm. This class talks with JanSelectFromTablePbClass
to achive the selections.
INSTANCE VARIABLES :
  bPickModalDialog : Default FALSE, This specifies if the pick screen should be modal or modeless.
  hWndChildTable : This is the handle of the child table window that is receiving the seleted values.
  sPickDialogName : string name of the pick screen ie ('dlgQItem').
  nLookUpMessage : Default PAM_LOOKUP, This is the message that gets sent first to hWndItem
                                  to try to pop the values of.  If a FALSE is returned ( ussually ) because the
                                  message is not implemented the PAM_LOOKUP is sent to the hWndChildTable
                                  if a FALSE is returned then PAM_LOOKUP is sent to the children of hWndChildTable.
                                  wParam of this message is one of two contstants SEL_OneToMany OR SEL_ManyToMany,
                                  lParam is the context row number
  bManyToManySelect : Default is TRUE, This allows multiple picked rows to be selected into multiple
                                     selected INTO (hWndChildTable) rows and when hWndChildTable rows selected
                                     run out the PAM_ADDROW is sent to insert new rows to retreive all the picked rows.
  bOneToManySelect : Default is FALSE, This allows one picked row to be selected into multiple selected
                                     into rows.
  bPAM_ADDROWOnManySelect : Default is TRUE, This speciefies that a PAM_ADDROW message
                                                       will be sent to the selected into table window when not enough
                                                       into selected rows are for the number of user picked rows.
